#Approach:

Square Root of a Number (Using Binary Search) – Hinglish Approach

Problem:
Given a positive integer n, find its square root.
If n perfect square nahi hai, to floor value return karni hai.

Why Binary Search?
Kyuki sqrt(n) ka answer range 1 se n ke beech hi hoga.
Aur hume fast solution chahiye -> O(log n)

Key Idea:
Hum aisa number x find karna chahte hain jiska square <= n ho
aur (x+1)^2 > n ho.
Wahi floor sqrt hoga.

Binary Search Logic:
Search space: 1 to n

mid = (low + high) / 2

Agar mid * mid == n
-> Perfect square -> return mid

Agar mid * mid < n
-> Answer right side mein ho sakta hai
-> Store mid as potential answer
-> low = mid + 1

Agar mid * mid > n
-> Square bada ho gaya
-> high = mid - 1

Loop ke end par jo last stored mid hoga wahi floor sqrt hoga.

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int floorSqrt(int n) {
        if(n == 0 || n == 1) return n;

        int low = 1;
        int high = n;
        int ans = 0;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            if((long)mid * mid == n){
                return mid;
            }
            else if((long)mid * mid < n){
                ans = mid;      // store possible answer
                low = mid + 1;
            }
            else{
                high = mid - 1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
